		<td><b>Re: NES output resolution</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Sure, but his point is that the phosphor layout is also a visible artifact, and the individual phosphor elements are often large enough to be important to the correct emulation of scanlines.<br /><br />I mean, not on a Trinitron tube (or <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=110013#p110013" class="postlink">my TV</a>). But for anything with the more conventional triangular electron gun arrangement...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


